help_text: The present_worth_factor and avg_critical_load are provided such that one can calculate an avoided outage cost in dollars by multiplying a value of load load ($/kWh) by the avg_critical_load, resilience_hours_avg, and present_worth_factor. Note that if the outage event is 'major' (i.e. only occurs once), then the present_worth_factor is 1.
